  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So he went to Indianapolis.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And it was at about that time that I was born.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My sister, Jacqueline, was the oldest child and she was born.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then, two years after Jacqueline, I was born, and then 18 months later, my sister, Dorothy Jean was born.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So there were two girls and a boy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would suggest, from what I-- I don't know, but I would suggest it was somewhere around 1919, 1920.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, my father was in World War I, and had-- had been gassed in service.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he was a disabled war veteran, and when he came north again-- he went back to the reservation after the war and then came to Marion.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was already carrying the problem of some sort of heart condition which he had as a result of the gassing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother, when she first came, did not work.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But because, I guess, the dire circumstances that they were in because of their lack of money because they found out very quickly that the amount of money they were paying my father really was-- didn't help them to live in the environment they were living in in Marion.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they were living in abject poverty, literally.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my father, who spoke Seminole and could read and write Seminole-- because the Seminoles were one of the few groups-- they called themselves one of the five 'civilized nations.' But he-- they had a written language.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he knew his own language and had been trained in all the other things that happened to Seminoles.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the one thing he didn't have was a-- was a-- was an English education.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother had-- my mother went back to school, evidently.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She was younger than my father.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
